On initialization LXAPI32 runs the script with the name "boot".
The root directory for all scripts should be defined with the environment
variable LXAPIROOT. All scripts are located in the etc subdirectory.
If LXAPIROOT is not defined LXAPI32 expects the root where the driver is
loaded from.

vmlinuz <parms>
	set <parms> for the kernel

init	<parms>
	set <parms> for init and do init
